
[1]victim

   VIC'TIM n. [L. victima.]

   1. A living being sacrificed to some deity, or in the performance of a
   religious rite; usually, some beast slain in sacrifice; but human
   beings have been slain by some nations, for the purpose of appeasing
   the wrath or conciliating the favor of some deity.

   2. Something destroyed; something sacrificed in the pursuit of an
   object. How many persons have fallen victims to jealousy, to lust, to
   ambition!
